Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora to moderate turn. Clay fine yellow-buff. Circular, irregular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. The clay suggests that it is from a Corinthian or Corinthian type jar.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1554)
